## [Version 2.1 - Accessibility & Mobile Enhancement] - 2025-10-28
### Added
- **Hamburger Menu Implementation:** Mobile navigation with smooth toggle functionality
- **ARIA Landmarks:** Added roles="navigation", "main", "banner", "contentinfo"
- **SEO Meta Tags:** Comprehensive meta description and keywords for better search visibility
- **Social Media Footer:** LinkedIn, Twitter, Facebook icons with proper links
- **Video Content Section:** Embedded video thumbnails with play functionality

### Changed
- **Mobile-First Approach:** Restructured CSS to prioritize mobile devices
- **Touch Interface:** Increased button sizes and touch targets for mobile users
- **Color Accessibility:** Enhanced contrast ratios meeting WCAG guidelines
- **Responsive Typography:** Scalable font sizes using clamp() and relative units

### Fixed
- **CSS Linking Issues:** Corrected file paths in all HTML documents
- **Content Quality:** Proofread and corrected all textual content
- **Image Optimization:** Added meaningful alt text to all visual elements
- **Cross-Browser Compatibility:** Tested and fixed rendering issues

### Technical Notes
- **CSS Path Verification:** Ensure CSS file location matches HTML reference
- **Cache Management:** Recommended hard refresh (Ctrl+F5) for testing
- **Syntax Validation:** CSS and HTML validated for errors

---

## [Version 2.0 - Part 2 Final] - 2025-10-23
### Feedback Implementation from Part 1
**Based on Part 1 Score: 75/100**
- **Fixed README Documentation:** Added all required information as per POE guide
- **Enhanced References:** Comprehensive and correctly formatted references added
- **Improved Changelog:** Detailed development record maintained
- **Navigation Fix:** Mobile navigation menu issues resolved

### CSS Styling - Desktop Implementation
#### External Stylesheet
- **Created and Implemented:** `style.css` correctly linked in all 7 HTML pages
- **Consistent Implementation:** Uniform styling across all pages (index.html, about.html, news.html, campaign.html, getinvolved.html, donate.html, contact.html)

#### Default Style Code
- **Comprehensive Base Styles:** CSS reset and default element styling
- **Consistent Application:** Font family (Arial, sans-serif), font sizes, color scheme applied throughout
- **Cohesive Design:** Unified look and feel across all website sections

#### Typography Styles
- **Hierarchical Text Styling:** h1 (2.5rem), h2 (2rem), h3 (1.5rem), p (1rem)
- **Font Properties:** Consistent font weights (300, 400, 700), line heights (1.6), letter spacing
- **Readability Enhancement:** Optimal contrast ratios and text alignment

#### Layout Structure
- **CSS Grid & Flexbox:** Modern layout techniques implemented
- **Proper Element Positioning:** Header, navigation, main content, footer correctly positioned
- **Visual Harmony:** Consistent spacing, alignment, and white space usage

#### Decoration and Color
- **Color Scheme:** Primary (#2c3e50), Secondary (#e74c3c), Accent (#3498db)
- **Decorative Elements:** Box shadows, borders, gradients, and hover effects
- **Visual Consistency:** Color palette applied uniformly across all interactive elements

#### Pseudo-Classes
- **Interactive States:** `:hover`, `:focus`, `:active` implemented for all interactive elements
- **Navigation Enhancement:** Menu items, buttons, and links with state-based styling
- **User Feedback:** Visual indicators for all user interactions

### Responsive Design Implementation
#### Media Queries/Breakpoints
- **Tablet Breakpoint:** `@media (max-width: 768px)`
- **Mobile Breakpoint:** `@media (max-width: 480px)`
- **Comprehensive Coverage:** All screen sizes addressed

#### Layout Adjustments
- **Mobile-First Approach:** Progressive enhancement from mobile to desktop
- **Flexible Grid Systems:** CSS Grid and Flexbox adaptations for different screens
- **Seamless Adaptation:** Layout restructures gracefully across devices

#### Typography Adjustments
- **Relative Units:** Use of rem/em for scalable typography
- **Viewport-Based Sizing:** vw/vh units for responsive text scaling
- **Readability Optimization:** Line lengths and font sizes adjusted for mobile

#### Navigation Menu Adjustments
- **Mobile Navigation Fix:** Resolved disappearing navigation on mobile screens
- **Hamburger Menu:** Implemented for mobile devices with smooth transitions
- **Touch-Friendly:** Larger tap targets for mobile users (44px minimum)

#### Image Adjustments
- **Responsive Images:** `max-width: 100%` and `height: auto`
- **Art Direction:** Different image crops for different screen sizes
- **Performance Optimization:** Appropriate image sizes for each breakpoint

### GitHub & Documentation
#### Commits
- **Multiple Descriptive Commits:** Regular commits with detailed messages
- **Feature-Based Committing:** Separate commits for styling, responsive design, fixes
- **Progress Tracking:** Clear commit history showing development progression

#### README Document
- **Comprehensive Information:** All required sections as per POE guide
- **Project Documentation:** Setup instructions, technologies, features, structure
- **User Guidance:** Clear explanations for developers and users

#### References
- **Complete Reference Section:** All sources properly cited and formatted
- **Resource Attribution:** CSS frameworks, code snippets, design inspiration
- **Academic Standards:** APA/MLA formatting as required

